column4: Does anyone have any ideas... when I use 'locate *~* | grep -v cache
Does anyone have any ideas... when I use 'locate *~* | grep -v cache' it says there is a file in Documents called Car Payments.txt~ but when I change directory to there, and use ls -a there isn't one
and if I just try rm on it, it says there isn't anything there.
your slocate.db might be out of date. Run "sudo updatedb" before running locate
